               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470510-name-1262" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1262" type="surname" value="SIMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1262" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SIMPSON</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 3rd of April I received information that the pri<lb></lb>soner was taking out more goods than he accounted for, and on the 4th of April I watched him, and saw that he was doing so—I told the inspector—he told me to watch him on the following morning, and I did—I saw the pri<lb></lb>soner and the foreman put the goods into the cart—the prisoner took the cart into the street—it was then taken to the station, and I found in it one dozen more than the prisoner had accounted for—he had done it by a very novel mode of packing—in the bottom tier of the crate he had managed to put four dozen and three bottles, four dozen and three in the middle tier, and in the top tier only four dozen—the officer found that also, and in consequence of that I gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> When the crates were empty we went to the stock of beer and filled them; when they were full we thought there were twelve dozen; we never counted them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470510-name-1263" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1263" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1263" type="surname" value="MANN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1263" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES MANN</persName>
                  </hi>. I drive for Mr. Simpson. I took out the boxes with the Prisoner—they ought to have held four dozen in each tier—he ordered me to unpack one box that we did not sell, and there were six bottles over—I told him it was wrong, and I would not allow it while he was out with me—he said it was all right, it was only six over.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184705100219"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did they go back to the factory? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, but then he took the money—we took out three boxes, and there were six over in each.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470510-name-1264" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470510-name-1264" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
